         <div type="translation" resp="part:argr part:sapi">
 	<p n="A1-A10"><!--début traduction sapi -->Hail ! There is <!-- j'ai ajouté une entrée pour madā, et ai traduit en fonction de votre traduction de C. 8, dans ECIC VIII--> the Y.P.K. Śrī Jaya-Indravarman prince Vak who was the son of the Y.P.K. Śrī Harivarman prince Paṅ, for this <foreign>candyam̃</foreign> protected the kingdom/reigned during one month. Then, because this Śrī Jaya-Indravarman had the nature of a child not yet <foreign>kam̃n</foreign> used to knowing the good and the bad things for <!--j'ai ajouté un deuxième "si" au lexique--> the protection of the kingdom/to reign and <supplied reason="subaudible">because</supplied> all the <!-- traduction de dunan kā avih difficile pour moi--> consequences of <supplied reason="subaudible">his</supplied> actions were devoided of justice with <supplied reason="subaudible">the way</supplied> he reigned also, then, this Y.P.K. Śrī Jaya-Indravarman and all the <foreign>senāpatī</foreign>, brahmans, astrologists <!--hora < horāvid?-->, pandits,
  masters of rituals, with all the women <!-- of the harem?--> of the Y.P.K. Śrī Harivarman <supplied reason="subaudible">made</supplied> the right judgment of looking for someone to become a <foreign>sī</foreign> who reigns. Then, they saw the <foreign>pu lyaṅ</foreign> Śrī Yuvarāja Mahāsenāpati, prince Paṅ<!--Là quelque chose ne va pas. Il semblerait qu'on puisse avoir un prince Thaṅ et un prince Paṅ, tous deux distincts.-->, who was the uncle <!-- Ici Finot dit que myak vient du cham moderne 'mik'= oncle. Mais dans A&C p. 389 (465 PDF), il est dit que ça veut dire tante maternelle.--> <foreign>prāṇa</foreign> of the Y.P.K. Śrī Jaya Indravarman <supplied reason="subaudible">and</supplied> who was the younger brother of this Y.P.K. Śrī Harivarmadeva. He has <!--madā ?--> full of the marks of a king conform with justice of the <foreign>pu pov tana rayā crakravartin</foreign> and this one knew the good and bad things, the <foreign>dharma</foreign>, the renunciation, the truthful speaking, the compassion for all beings, all.... </p>

  <p n="B1-B5">Fortune! There is <!-- j'ai ajouté une entrée pour madā, et ai traduit en fonction de votre traduction de C. 8, dans ECIC VIII--> one king <!--traduction pu pom̃ tana rayā s(ā) driy·--> namely Y.P.K. Śrī Jaya Indravarman, who is the absolute paramount sovereign. The plot/location where he was born is in the <foreign>lamvīṅ</foreign><!-- A&C f438 (pdf p. 514), lamvī = anthroponyme : vinai lamvī --> of Campapura. He is from a superior and righteous lineage on both sides<!-- Ici j'ai changé l'ordre des mots pour la traduction-->. And Y.P.K. Śrī Jaya Indravarman is endowed with the thirty-two marks, in contact<!-- maknā < knā ?. Cela fait penser à : A&C f387 (pdf p. 463) mapaknā < knā, paknā ?--> with grace, beauty, youthfulness, ability, cleverness/skilfulness, great virtues, braveness from birth, competence with all the weapons, great valour.
  </p>
